summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous relevant resolutions, including 687 (1991), 689 (1991), 806 (1993), 833 (1993) and 1483 (2003),
Noting the Secretary-General's report on UNIKOM (S/2003/656),
Reaffirming Iraq and Kuwait's sovereignty and territorial integrity,
Recognizing that UNIKOM and a demilitarized zone are no longer necessary,
Appreciating Kuwait's voluntary contributions and commending UNIKOM's role,
Decides to:
1. Continue UNIKOM's mandate until 6 October 2003;
2. Transfer UNIKOM's non-removable property and assets to Kuwait and Iraq;
3. End the demilitarized zone on 6 October 2003;
4. Request the Secretary-General to report on UNIKOM's mandate completion;
5. Appreciate Kuwait's decision to defray two-thirds of the Observation Mission's cost since 1 November 1993;
6. Remain seized of the matter.
